15#include <functional>
16#include <memory>

18
19#include "api/transport/network_control.h"
20#include "api/transport/webrtc_key_value_config.h"
21#include "modules/remote_bitrate_estimator/include/remote_bitrate_estimator.h"

23#include "rtc_base/experiments/field_trial_parser.h"
24#include "rtc_base/numerics/sequence_number_util.h"
25#include "rtc_base/synchronization/mutex.h"
26
27namespace webrtc {
28
29class Clock;
30namespace rtcp {
31class TransportFeedback;
32}
33
34// Class used when send-side BWE is enabled: This proxy is instantiated on the
35// receive side. It buffers a number of receive timestamps and then sends
36// transport feedback messages back too the send side.
37class RemoteEstimatorProxy : public RemoteBitrateEstimator {
38 public:
39 // Used for sending transport feedback messages when send side
40 // BWE is used.
41 using TransportFeedbackSender = std::function<void(
42 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<rtcp::RtcpPacket>> packets)>;
43 RemoteEstimatorProxy(Clock* clock,
44 TransportFeedbackSender feedback_sender,
45 const WebRtcKeyValueConfig* key_value_config,
46 NetworkStateEstimator* network_state_estimator);
47 ~RemoteEstimatorProxy() override;
48
49 void IncomingPacket(int64_t arrival_time_ms,
50 size_t payload_size,
51 const RTPHeader& header) override;
52 void RemoveStream(uint32_t ssrc) override {}
53 bool LatestEstimate(std::vector<unsigned int>* ssrcs,
54 unsigned int* bitrate_bps) const override;
55 void OnRttUpdate(int64_t avg_rtt_ms, int64_t max_rtt_ms) override {}
56 void SetMinBitrate(int min_bitrate_bps) override {}
57 int64_t TimeUntilNextProcess() override;
58 void Process() override;
59 void OnBitrateChanged(int bitrate);
60 void SetSendPeriodicFeedback(bool send_periodic_feedback);
61
62 private:
63 struct TransportWideFeedbackConfig {
64 FieldTrialParameter<TimeDelta> back_window{"wind", TimeDelta::Millis(500)};
65 FieldTrialParameter<TimeDelta> min_interval{"min", TimeDelta::Millis(50)};
66 FieldTrialParameter<TimeDelta> max_interval{"max", TimeDelta::Millis(250)};
67 FieldTrialParameter<TimeDelta> default_interval{"def",
68 TimeDelta::Millis(100)};
69 FieldTrialParameter<double> bandwidth_fraction{"frac", 0.05};
70 explicit TransportWideFeedbackConfig(
71 const WebRtcKeyValueConfig* key_value_config) {
72 ParseFieldTrial({&back_window, &min_interval, &max_interval,
73 &default_interval, &bandwidth_fraction},
74 key_value_config->Lookup(
75 "WebRTC-Bwe-TransportWideFeedbackIntervals"));
76 }
77 };
78
79 void MaybeCullOldPackets(int64_t sequence_number, int64_t arrival_time_ms)
80 RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(&lock_);
81 void SendPeriodicFeedbacks() RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(&lock_);
82 void SendFeedbackOnRequest(int64_t sequence_number,
83 const FeedbackRequest& feedback_request)
84 RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(&lock_);
85
86 // Returns a Transport Feedback packet with information about as many packets
87 // that has been received between [`begin_sequence_number_incl`,
88 // `end_sequence_number_excl`) that can fit in it. If `is_periodic_update`,
89 // this represents sending a periodic feedback message, which will make it
90 // update the `periodic_window_start_seq_` variable with the first packet that
91 // was not included in the feedback packet, so that the next update can
92 // continue from that sequence number.
93 //
94 // If no incoming packets were added, nullptr is returned.
95 //
96 // `include_timestamps` decide if the returned TransportFeedback should
97 // include timestamps.
98 std::unique_ptr<rtcp::TransportFeedback> MaybeBuildFeedbackPacket(
99 bool include_timestamps,
100 int64_t begin_sequence_number_inclusive,
101 int64_t end_sequence_number_exclusive,
102 bool is_periodic_update) RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(&lock_);
103
104 Clock* const clock_;
105 const TransportFeedbackSender feedback_sender_;
106 const TransportWideFeedbackConfig send_config_;
107 int64_t last_process_time_ms_;
108
109 Mutex lock_;
110 // |network_state_estimator_| may be null.
111 NetworkStateEstimator* const network_state_estimator_
112 RTC_PT_GUARDED_BY(&lock_);
113 uint32_t media_ssrc_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(&lock_);
114 uint8_t feedback_packet_count_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(&lock_);
115 SeqNumUnwrapper<uint16_t> unwrapper_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(&lock_);
116
117 // The next sequence number that should be the start sequence number during
118 // periodic reporting. Will be absl::nullopt before the first seen packet.
119 absl::optional<int64_t> periodic_window_start_seq_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(&lock_);
120
121 // Packet arrival times, by sequence number.
122 PacketArrivalTimeMap packet_arrival_times_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(&lock_);
123
124 int64_t send_interval_ms_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(&lock_);
125 bool send_periodic_feedback_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(&lock_);
126
127 // Unwraps absolute send times.
128 uint32_t previous_abs_send_time_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(&lock_);
129 Timestamp abs_send_timestamp_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(&lock_);
130};
131
132} // namespace webrtc
